            <title>[LU-11689] lfs project should proceed all dirs if hit errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11689</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt; Leftover fix since &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10986&quot; title=&quot; make lfs project tolerant errors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10986&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10986&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lfs: make lfs project tolerant errors&lt;br/&gt;
    We should proceed other dirs if we hit errors, otherwise,&lt;br/&gt;
    some dirtree like following will fail if aaaa not exists.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    testdir/&lt;br/&gt;
    &#9500;&#9472;&#9472; subdir&lt;br/&gt;
    &#9474;&#160;&#160; &#9492;&#9472;&#9472; 1&lt;br/&gt;
    &#9500;&#9472;&#9472; bbbb -&amp;gt; aaaa&lt;br/&gt;
    &#9492;&#9472;&#9472; cccc&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
